parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring perch can cause the front end of the vehicle to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud banging or crashing noise
front end of the vehicle dropping or collapsing
vibration in the front suspension
and loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Deployment and Shift Lever Explosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags and the explosion of the shift lever can cause injuries, accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags deploy inadvertedly
shift lever explodes
and smoke emits from the console.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected retraction of the seatbelt can cause physical harm to the occupants, including chest injuries, breathing difficulties, and potentially even cardiac arrest. This can also lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Loud explosion or popping noise
seatbelt suddenly and forcefully tightens or retracts
occupants are pinned back into their seats
seatbelt does not retract after the incident
SRS warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause physical harm to the driver and passengers, and may lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without a crash or impact
loud noise
pressure on the chest or torso
burning smell
smoke in the cabin
seatbelt tightening or retracting abnormally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash
injury or fatality occurs.
